    "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add MiniMax-M2.7 (https://huggingface.co/MiniMaxAI/MiniMax-M2.7) accuracy (GSM8K 5-shot) and performance (`bench_one_batch`) nightly CI tests for AMD MI30x (MI325/MI300X)\n- MiniMax-M2.7 shares the same `MiniMaxM2ForCausalLM` architecture as M2.5 with identical MoE config (256 experts, 8 active), using TP8+EP8 server configuration with `aiter` attention backend\n- Replace M2.5 nightly CI jobs with M2.7 on MI30x (M2.5 test files kept in repo, just not run in nightly)\n- MI35x test files created but not wired to nightly jobs yet (pending more MI35x runners)\n- Fix broken import in `minimax_m2.py`: `get_bool_env_var` was imported from `sglang.srt.distributed` but is defined in `sglang.srt.utils.common` (introduced by #20673, breaks all MiniMax M2 models on current main — [M2.5 also fails](https://github.com/sgl-project/sglang/actions/runs/24358226838/job/71130716099))\n\n### Test Files\n| File | Platform | Type | Suite | Nightly |\n|------|----------|------|-------|---------|\n| `test/registered/amd/accuracy/mi30x/test_minimax_m27_eval_amd.py` | MI30x | Accuracy | `nightly-amd-accuracy-8-gpu-minimax-m27` | :white_check_mark: active |\n| `test/registered/amd/perf/mi30x/test_minimax_m27_perf_amd.py` | MI30x | Perf | `nightly-perf-8-gpu-minimax-m27` | :white_check_mark: active |\n| `test/registered/amd/accuracy/mi35x/test_minimax_m27_eval_mi35x.py` | MI35x | Accuracy | `nightly-amd-8-gpu-mi35x-minimax-m27` | :no_entry_sign: not wired (pending runners) |\n| `test/registered/amd/perf/mi35x/test_minimax_m27_perf_mi35x.py` | MI35x | Perf | `nightly-perf-8-gpu-mi35x-minimax-m27` | :no_entry_sign: not wired (pending runners) |\n\n### Workflow Changes\nBoth `nightly-test-amd.yml` and `nightly-test-amd-rocm720.yml` updated:\n- Remove M2.5 MI30x + MI35x job definitions, dropdown options, and `check-all-jobs.needs` entries\n- Add M2.7 MI30x job definitions (accuracy + perf combined), dropdown options, and `check-all-jobs.needs` entries\n\n### Bug Fix\n`python/sglang/srt/models/minimax_m2.py`: moved `get_bool_env_var` import from `sglang.srt.distributed` to `sglang.srt.utils.common`. Without this fix, the native MiniMax M2 model fails to register during import, causing fallback to the transformers wrapper which crashes on `config.rope_parameters`.\n\n## CI Results (all pass)\n\n- **Default ROCm**: https://github.com/sgl-project/sglang/actions/runs/24362746024\n- **ROCm 7.2**: https://github.com/sgl-project/sglang/actions/runs/24362746633\n\n| Job | Status |\n|-----|--------|\n| `nightly-8-gpu-minimax-m27` (MI30x) | :white_check_mark: passed |\n| `nightly-8-gpu-mi35x-minimax-m27` (MI35x) | :white_check_mark: passed |\n| `nightly-8-gpu-minimax-m27-rocm720` (MI30x, ROCm 7.2) | :white_check_mark: passed |\n| `nightly-8-gpu-mi35x-minimax-m27-rocm720` (MI35x, ROCm 7.2) | :white_check_mark: passed |\n\n## MiniMax-M2.7 Accuracy Results (GSM8K 5-shot, 200 questions)\n\n| Platform | Accuracy | Threshold | Status |\n|----------|----------|-----------|--------|\n| MI30x (MI325) | 0.935 | 0.93 | PASS |\n| MI35x | 0.960 | 0.93 | PASS |\n\n## MiniMax-M2.7 Performance Results (input_len=4096, output_len=512)\n\n### MI30x (MI325)\n\n| batch size | input len | latency (s) | input throughput (tok/s) | output throughput (tok/s) | ITL (ms) |\n| ---------- | --------- | ----------- | ------------------------ | ------------------------- | -------- |\n| 1 | 4096 | 6.07 | 8704.99 | 91.39 | 10.94 |\n| 8 | 4096 | 8.16 | 25272.66 | 597.08 | 13.40 |\n| 16 | 4096 | 9.13 | 44146.36 | 1072.14 | 14.92 |\n| 64 | 4096 | 14.11 | 60731.52 | 3347.34 | 19.12 |\n\n### MI35x\n\n| batch size | input len | latency (s) | input throughput (tok/s) | output throughput (tok/s) | ITL (ms) |\n| ---------- | --------- | ----------- | ------------------------ | ------------------------- | -------- |\n| 1 | 4096 | 4.35 | 44039.82 | 120.32 | 8.31 |\n| 8 | 4096 | 5.54 | 80291.27 | 798.56 | 10.02 |\n| 16 | 4096 | 6.53 | 81585.24 | 1430.34 | 11.19 |\n| 64 | 4096 | 10.99 | 85850.02 | 4129.25 | 15.50 |\n\n### Comparison vs M2.5 (MI30x, Apr 12 nightly)\n\n| batch size | M2.5 output tput | M2.7 output tput | M2.5 ITL | M2.7 ITL |\n| ---------- | ---------------- | ---------------- | -------- | -------- |\n| 1 | 91.83 tok/s | 91.39 tok/s | 10.89 ms | 10.94 ms |\n| 8 | 598.30 tok/s | 597.08 tok/s | 13.37 ms | 13.40 ms |\n| 16 | 1075.49 tok/s | 1072.14 tok/s | 14.88 ms | 14.92 ms |\n| 64 | 3033.94 tok/s | **3347.34 tok/s (+10.3%)** | 21.09 ms | **19.12 ms (-9.3%)** |\n\nPerformance is on par at small batch sizes. At batch_size=64, M2.7 shows +10% output throughput and -9% ITL, likely due to native FP8 quantization.",
